span.strong: Welcome to the Harrisburg School District

strong.style: text-align: center; font-family: Tahoma; font-size: medium;

span.style: font-family: Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(192, 0, 0);

strong.span: HBGSD LAUNCHES PLANNED ACADEMIC ENRICHMENT WITH 40 HOURS OF TELEVISED ENGLISH LANGUAGE ARTS AND MATHEMATICS PROGRAMMING ON WHBG-TV 20

span.br: Dear Harrisburg School District Parents and Guardians:

p.span:
The Harrisburg School District, in partnership with WHBG-TV 20 and the City of Harrisburg, is pleased to offer more than 40 hours of K – 8th grade planned academic enrichment television broadcasting on channel 20 for Comcast customers, the District’s Facebook page, and YouTube channel.
The daily (Monday-Friday) broadcasting schedule includes recorded lessons from our teachers and streamed lessons in the areas of English Language Arts for K – 5th grade students and Mathematics for 1st – 8th grade students, which will be broadcasted daily across three media platforms.

strong.span: K – 5th GRADE FRIDAY, APRIL 17 BROADCASTING SCHEDULE FOR ENGLISH, READING, WRITING, AND LANGUAGE ARTS
1st – 8th GRADE FRIDAY, APRIL 17 BROADCASTING SCHEDULE FOR MATHEMATICS

span.br:
Students in Pre-K – 12th grade will continue to have access to high quality planned academic enrichment via the District's partnership with WITF and its PBS Kids and PBS Prime Time educational programming for English Language Arts, Mathematics, and Science.
The Harrisburg School District is committed to providing meaningful academic enrichment and at home learning opportunities for all students in Pre-K through 12th grade for the duration of the COVID-19 crisis.

strong.span: NEW SCHEDULE FOR GRAB & GO MEALS AND FAMILY FOOD BOXES

p.span: Beginning Tuesday, April 14, 2020, the Harrisburg School District will provide five (5) “Grab and Go” breakfasts and five (5) lunch meals for students on Tuesdays ONLY from 11:00 am to 12:30 pm. Meals and food boxes will be distributed at the following Harrisburg School District locations.

The Central Pennsylvania Food Bank and the Harrisburg Bureau of Police will provide free family food on a first come, first served basis on Thursdays ONLY at 4:00 pm at sites listed above and at the Heinz-Menaker Center.

div.p: The Harrisburg School District does not discriminate on the basis of race, color, religious creed, ancestry, age, familial status, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, or disability. The policy of equal opportunity and equitable treatment applies to every aspect of school district operations and activities, including admissions and employment practices. This policy shall be made known to all persons and organizations associated with the Harrisburg School District, to all Educational Placement Services, the Pennsylvania Bureau of Employment Security and all recruiting sources. Any student, parent, employee, or citizen who feels that they have been denied fair treatment or equal opportunity in any aspect of School District operations or activities because of race, color, religious creed, ancestry, age, familial status, sex, national origin, sexual orientation, or disability should contact the Title IX Compliance Coordinator, Ms. Merry-Grace Majors, at the Harrisburg School District Administration Building, 1601 State Street, Harrisburg, PA 17103 or phone (717) 703-4024. The Harrisburg School District is an Equal Opportunity Employer. Auxiliary aids and services are available upon request.
